# Exercise 005 - Download AWX and install it with docker compose method

0) Disable SELinux, firewalld and restart docker service;

1) Install epel-release package;

2) Install ansible, git and python-pip packages to satisfy requirements;

3) Install docker-compose via python pip;

4) Clone the https://github.com/ansible/awx git repo locally;

5) Start the ansible build by going into the awx/installer dir and launching:

ansible-playbook -i inventory -e docker_registry_password=password install.yml

6) Check the running containers;

7) Go with a browser to the address of your server and login into the AWX
   console with the admin/password credentials;
